claim.claim-text:
28. A method for securely receiving material from a licensor of the material, comprising:
receiving a license to use material;
receiving a plurality of license keys corresponding to said license;
receiving said material in at least one MPEG-4 bit stream encrypted by a plurality of content keys for corresponding time periods of said material;
receiving said plurality of content keys encrypted with said plurality of license keys, used one-at-a-time on a periodically rotating basis for encrypting and decrypting said plurality of content keys, in an Intellectual Property Management and Protection (IPMP) stream provided along with said material;
decrypting said encrypted plurality of content keys using said plurality of license keys; and
decrypting said encrypted material using said decrypted plurality of content keys for corresponding time periods of said material.
